etymologies: 1970s; earliest use found in True. From late Sanskrit premī, nominative singular of premin imbued with love, probably punningly after PremPal Rawat, given name of Guru Maharaj Ji (b. 1957; later known as Maharaji); compare -ie

definitions: A follower of the Guru Maharaj Ji, or of the religious organization Divine Light Mission founded by him.

notes.text: Following a schism, the Maharaj Ji's part of the movement was renamed Elan Vital in 1984.
